<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.190982>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Keilbachia acumina sp. n. (A paratype from Higashi-ichiki, B paratype from Iriomote, C paratype from Mt. Aso, E and D holotype, F paratype from Tsurugizaki). Maxillary palpus (A) in lateral view, antennal flagellomere 4 (B) in lateral view, apex of front tibia (C) in prolateral view, part of hypopygium (D), gonostylus (E) and apex of gonostylus (F) in ventral view. Scale for B 0.05 mm, for others 0.10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/190982/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

